<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does refrigerator repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Our diagnostic fee is $89 — and that's applied toward the repair the moment you approve the work. Most refrigerator repairs in LA run between $150 and $400 depending on the part and the brand. Compressor replacements on luxury brands like Sub-Zero or Thermador run higher. We give you a full written estimate before any work begins. No surprises on the invoice."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you repair my refrigerator the same day in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — same day is our standard, not a premium. We have technicians dispatched across Los Angeles daily, covering areas from Silver Lake to Santa Monica to Burbank. Call us before noon and we can typically be there that afternoon. We stock the most commonly needed parts so the majority of repairs are completed on the first visit."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair Sub-Zero and Thermador refrigerators?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Sub-Zero and Thermador are two of the brands our technicians work on most frequently in LA. We use OEM parts specifically sourced for these units — not generic substitutes. Sub-Zero sealed system issues, Thermador cooling failures, Viking compressor problems — we carry parts for these on the van so most repairs don't require a second visit."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does your refrigerator repair warranty cover?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Every refrigerator repair we complete comes with a 90-day warranty on both parts and labor. If the same issue comes back within that window, we come back and fix it at no charge. We back this up in writing before we leave."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My refrigerator is making a loud noise — is it serious?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "It depends on where the noise is coming from and what it sounds like. A buzzing from the back usually points to the condenser fan motor. Clicking from inside means evaporator fan or defrost timer. A grinding or knocking sound from the bottom can be the compressor — that one you don't want to ignore. Call us and describe what you're hearing — we can often narrow it down before we arrive."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My fridge runs but doesn't cool — what's wrong?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "This is the most common call we get. In LA's warm climate, condenser coils clogged with dust are a major culprit — the fridge works hard but can't shed heat. Beyond that: evaporator fan failure, a sealed system problem (refrigerant leak or compressor), or a faulty thermostat. Our technicians carry diagnostic tools to identify the root cause, not just patch the symptom."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair commercial refrigerators and restaurant equipment?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. We repair commercial refrigerators, walk-in coolers, and restaurant refrigeration throughout Los Angeles. Our commercial diagnostic fee is $120. We work on True, Traulsen, Turbo Air, Hoshizaki, and other commercial brands. Business downtime is a real cost — we treat commercial calls with the same urgency as residential."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

