        <div class="repair-detail">Deep-cleaned condenser coils, replaced worn door gasket on the refrigerator side (was letting warm air in), checked refrigerant charge. Unit back to normal cycle within the hour.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-card">
        <div class="repair-title">Silver Lake · LG Bottom-Freezer</div>
        <h3>"Water pooling under the crisper drawers every morning"</h3>
        <p>Clogged defrost drain — the defrost water had nowhere to go and was backing up into the refrigerator compartment. On LG bottom-freezer models the drain tube routes behind the back panel and is prone to ice buildup that blocks it. This isn't a DIY fix because accessing it means removing shelving and the back panel.</p>
        <div class="repair-detail">Cleared and flushed defrost drain, checked defrost heater function to prevent recurrence, verified drain outlet was clear. No recurrence reported.</div>
